-{"id":"bd-3uqs","title":"Shared SSH Command Execution Infrastructure","description":"## Overview
Create robust, reusable SSH command execution utilities that all fleet operations depend on.
This is foundational infrastructure that run_preflight(), get_fleet_status(), and rollback_workers()
will all leverage.

## IMPORTANT: Relationship to Existing Code

### Existing SSH Helpers in executor.rs
executor.rs currently has these SSH helpers (lines 342-399):
- \`test_ssh_connectivity(&worker_config)\`
- \`create_remote_directory(&worker_config)\`
- \`copy_binary_via_scp(&worker_config, path)\`
- \`set_executable_permissions(&worker_config)\`
- \`verify_installation(&worker_config)\`

### Our Approach: EXTRACT AND GENERALIZE
1. **Extract** the SSH command execution pattern from executor.rs into a reusable SshExecutor
2. **Generalize** it to run arbitrary commands with timeout and structured output
3. **Keep** the existing executor.rs helpers but have them use SshExecutor internally
4. **Don't duplicate** - refactor, don't rewrite

### Example Refactoring
\`\`\`rust
// BEFORE (in executor.rs):
async fn test_ssh_connectivity(worker: &WorkerConfig) -> Result<()> {
    let output = Command::new("ssh")
        .args(["-o", "BatchMode=yes", ...])
        .output()
        .await?;
    // ...
}

// AFTER (executor.rs uses SshExecutor):
async fn test_ssh_connectivity(worker: &WorkerConfig) -> Result<()> {
    let ssh = SshExecutor::new(worker, CONNECT_TIMEOUT);
    ssh.check_connectivity().await?;
    Ok(())
}
\`\`\`

## Technical Requirements

### 1. Core SSH Executor
\`\`\`rust
pub struct SshExecutor {
    worker: WorkerConfig,
    timeout: Duration,
    connect_timeout: Duration,
}

impl SshExecutor {
    pub fn new(worker: &WorkerConfig, timeout: Duration) -> Self;
    pub async fn run_command(&self, cmd: &str) -> Result<CommandOutput, FleetError>;
    pub async fn run_command_raw(&self, cmd: &str) -> Result<String, FleetError>;
    pub async fn check_connectivity(&self) -> Result<bool, FleetError>;
}

pub struct CommandOutput {
    pub stdout: String,
    pub stderr: String,
    pub exit_code: i32,
    pub duration: Duration,
}
\`\`\`

### 2. SSH Options Builder
Consistent SSH options across all operations (match existing executor.rs patterns):
- StrictHostKeyChecking configuration (from WorkerConfig)
- ConnectTimeout (default: 10s)
- ServerAliveInterval / ServerAliveCountMax for long operations
- BatchMode=yes for non-interactive execution
- IdentityFile support
- ProxyJump/ProxyCommand support (from WorkerConfig)

### 3. Error Handling
Create specific error variants:
- ConnectionTimeout: SSH connection couldn't be established
- CommandTimeout: Command started but didn't complete in time
- AuthenticationFailed: Key/password rejected
- HostUnreachable: Network-level failure
- CommandFailed { exit_code, stderr }: Command ran but failed

### 4. Output Parsing Utilities
\`\`\`rust
pub fn parse_disk_space(df_output: &str) -> Result<u64, ParseError>;
pub fn parse_version_string(version_output: &str) -> Result<String, ParseError>;
\`\`\`

## CRITICAL: Detailed Logging Requirements

All SSH operations MUST have comprehensive tracing logs:

\`\`\`rust
// Before SSH connection
tracing::debug!(
    worker = %self.worker.id,
    host = %self.worker.host,
    command = %cmd,
    timeout_ms = %self.timeout.as_millis(),
    "Executing SSH command"
);

// On success
tracing::info!(
    worker = %self.worker.id,
    command = %cmd,
    exit_code = %output.exit_code,
    duration_ms = %output.duration.as_millis(),
    stdout_len = %output.stdout.len(),
    stderr_len = %output.stderr.len(),
    "SSH command completed"
);

// On timeout
tracing::warn!(
    worker = %self.worker.id,
    host = %self.worker.host,
    command = %cmd,
    timeout_ms = %self.timeout.as_millis(),
    "SSH command timed out"
);

// On failure
tracing::error!(
    worker = %self.worker.id,
    host = %self.worker.host,
    command = %cmd,
    error = %e,
    "SSH command failed"
);
\`\`\`

## File Location
Create: rch/src/fleet/ssh.rs
Export from: rch/src/fleet/mod.rs
Refactor: rch/src/fleet/executor.rs (use SshExecutor instead of raw Command)

## Design Principles
1. **Fail-open philosophy**: SSH failures should not block local compilation
2. **Timeouts everywhere**: Every SSH operation has a timeout
3. **Structured errors**: Parse stderr into actionable error types
4. **Testability**: Mock-friendly design (trait-based) for unit testing
5. **Observable**: Rich tracing logs for debugging
6. **Don't duplicate**: Refactor existing code to use new infrastructure

## Testing Strategy
- Unit tests with MockSshExecutor (bd-3uqs.1)
- Integration tests against localhost (if SSH enabled)
- Timeout behavior tests with deliberate slow commands
- Log output verification tests

## References
- Existing helpers in executor.rs:342-399 (TO BE REFACTORED)
- WorkerConfig structure in rch-common/src/worker.rs
- Error handling patterns in rch/src/error.rs

## Success Criteria
- [ ] SshExecutor struct with configurable timeouts
- [ ] SSH options builder matching existing executor.rs patterns
- [ ] At least 5 error variants for different failure modes
- [ ] Output parsing utilities for disk and version
- [ ] Comprehensive tracing logs at debug/info/warn/error levels
- [ ] executor.rs refactored to use SshExecutor (no duplication)
- [ ] Unit tests with >80% coverage
- [ ] No unsafe code, no panics","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T17:49:57.774455882Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-30T18:07:02.414205530Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["infrastructure"]}
